    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for runc.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The runC tool is a lightweight, portable implementation of the Open Container Format (OCF) that provides container runtime.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* runc: container escape via 'masked path' abuse due to mount race conditions (CVE-2025-31133)\n\n* runc: container escape with malicious config due to /dev/console mount and related races (CVE-2025-52565)\n\n* runc: container escape and denial of service due to arbitrary write gadgets and procfs write redirects (CVE-2025-52881)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
